						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in the ruined Durgā temple.</p>						

						<p>1493 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record registers a gift by Dēvarāya-voḍeya. But all details are lost.</p>						

						<p>It is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Pramādīcha, Chaitra, śu. 9, Tuesday.</hi> Palaeographically the record may be assigned to the 15th century in which case the details correspond to 1493 A.D., March 26 which might be date intended.</p>						

						</summary>
